339
03:00:23,960 --> 03:00:25,400
-Oh, my God.

340
03:00:25,390 --> 03:00:28,160
Uh, Casper, um...

341
03:00:28,160 --> 03:00:30,960
I'm sorry, I can't.

342
03:00:30,960 --> 03:00:32,060
-W-what?

343
03:00:32,060 --> 03:00:35,000
-I'm having so much fun, Danny!

344
03:00:35,000 --> 03:00:38,340
-I'm so glad, Bryce.

345
03:00:38,340 --> 03:00:40,140
-I can't say yes right now.

346
03:00:40,140 --> 03:00:42,610
-Bryce, Danny,
wait up, fast pokes!

347
03:00:44,980 --> 03:00:46,810
-Uh, why can't you say yes?

348
03:00:46,810 --> 03:00:49,310
-I don't know.
It just doesn't feel right yet.

349
03:00:49,320 --> 03:00:51,820
-You guys, you guys, look --
I'm a plane.

350
03:00:53,390 --> 03:00:55,890
-I mean, do you think
that we're ready?

351
03:00:55,890 --> 03:00:58,890
-Hey! I know you!
-Hey! I know you!

352
03:00:58,890 --> 03:01:00,190
-Get back here!

353
03:01:01,530 --> 03:01:04,370
-Please, say something, Casper.

354
03:01:04,360 --> 03:01:07,800
-Those three men
are having the best time.

355
03:01:07,800 --> 03:01:09,570
-What?
-Those guys,

356
03:01:09,570 --> 03:01:12,270
I've never seen grown men having
such, like, genuine, pure fun.

357
03:01:12,270 --> 03:01:13,970
Like, how old are they?

358
03:01:13,970 --> 03:01:16,010
-Um, this train
lost its caboose.

359
03:01:16,010 --> 03:01:18,010
-Yeah, Danny, why'd you let go?

360
03:01:18,010 --> 03:01:20,310
-Because I was laughing
too much.

361
03:01:20,310 --> 03:01:22,680
God, I love being in my 40s.

362
03:01:24,280 --> 03:01:26,080
-They're in their 40s?

363
03:01:26,090 --> 03:01:28,930
-Okay. I'm so glad that's what
you're focused on right now.

364
03:01:28,920 --> 03:01:30,590
-Sorry if I'm a little
scattered, Candace.

365
03:01:30,590 --> 03:01:32,330
You just told me
you didn't love me.

366
03:01:32,330 --> 03:01:34,730
-Stop it!
You know that I love you!

367
03:01:34,730 --> 03:01:36,830
-Eeeeeeeee!

368
03:01:39,000 --> 03:01:41,270
And I know I'm gonna be
with you forever.

369
03:01:41,270 --> 03:01:43,610
-Oh, I feel so free!

370
03:01:43,600 --> 03:01:46,140
I feel like Alysa Liu right now.

371
03:01:48,470 --> 03:01:49,740
-I just don't know

372
03:01:49,740 --> 03:01:51,340
if I'm ready to start
forever right now.

373
03:01:51,340 --> 03:01:52,670
-Ooh-wah! Ooh-wah!

374
03:01:52,680 --> 03:01:53,680
Is that your girlfriend?

375
03:01:53,680 --> 03:01:55,480
Hunh, aah!

376
03:01:56,850 --> 03:01:58,290
-Sorry. What did you say?

377
03:01:58,280 --> 03:02:00,350
-See? See? This is
what I'm talking about.

378
03:02:00,350 --> 03:02:02,650
I'm always fighting
for your attention.

379
03:02:02,660 --> 03:02:05,800
-I'm sorry. I can't
get a read on these guys.

380
03:02:05,790 --> 03:02:08,830
-Best bachelor party ever!

381
03:02:08,830 --> 03:02:11,030
-This is a bachelor party?

382
03:02:11,030 --> 03:02:13,200
-I cannot believe you
right now!

383
03:02:13,200 --> 03:02:15,800
-Candace, come on!
Don't cry.

384
03:02:15,800 --> 03:02:20,740
-Oh, my gosh, you guys,
look who finally showed up.

385
03:02:20,740 --> 03:02:24,010
-Hudson!
-Hudson!

386
03:02:24,010 --> 03:02:26,280
Yeah, dude!

387
03:02:26,280 --> 03:02:28,450
Hudson!

388
03:02:28,450 --> 03:02:30,220
-Hudson.

389
03:02:30,220 --> 03:02:33,060
-Dude, so stoked.

390
03:02:33,050 --> 03:02:35,950
-Hudson! Yeah!

391
03:02:40,130 --> 03:02:42,260
-Oh! Sorry.

392
03:02:42,260 --> 03:02:44,830
-Oh.

393
03:02:44,830 --> 03:02:46,070
So glad you're here, Hudson.

394
03:02:46,070 --> 03:02:49,140
-I know.
It's pretty great. Hey.

395
03:02:49,140 --> 03:02:51,910
Sorry I'm late, fellas,

396
03:02:51,910 --> 03:02:54,080
but I have a serious question.

397
03:02:54,070 --> 03:02:55,070
-Yeah.

398
03:02:56,880 --> 03:02:58,410
-Who's ready
to skate their butts off?

399
03:02:58,410 --> 03:03:00,880
-Yeah!
-Hudson!

400
03:03:00,880 --> 03:03:02,880
-Hudson's hilarious.

401
03:03:02,880 --> 03:03:04,620
-And a lot of my issues
are my own.

402
03:03:04,620 --> 03:03:07,360
Like, sometimes I think
that I don't deserve you,

403
03:03:07,350 --> 03:03:09,390
and you've just got
so much on your plate.

404
03:03:09,390 --> 03:03:11,830
It's like, who am I,
you know?

405
03:03:11,820 --> 03:03:13,150
-Ooh-wee! Ooh-wee!

406
03:03:13,160 --> 03:03:15,700
-♪ Come on, ride the train,
and ride it ♪

407
03:03:15,700 --> 03:03:17,400
-Choo-choo!

408
03:03:17,400 --> 03:03:19,370
-I've never felt so cool!

409
03:03:22,340 --> 03:03:23,980
-How's that even possible?

410
03:03:23,970 --> 03:03:26,070
-I don't know.
It's just how I feel.

411
03:03:26,070 --> 03:03:27,570
-No, I -- sorry.
I meant, like,

412
03:03:27,570 --> 03:03:29,240
how is ice-skating
in a four-person train

413
03:03:29,240 --> 03:03:31,640
the coolest
that that guy has ever felt?

414
03:03:31,650 --> 03:03:33,950
-Stop using those guys
as a distraction

415
03:03:33,950 --> 03:03:36,020
and talk to me, Casper!

416
03:03:36,020 --> 03:03:39,190
-♪ Ice-skate like an Egyptian ♪

417
